{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775872016354,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a387fde001l4yHK7aI722mf7","messageID":"msg_d7a38796e0018bSMMQESSdUqJe","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872062807,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3934b3001SxXMndcTkgnZ92","messageID":"msg_d7a38796e0018bSMMQESSdUqJe","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-822230c5202f4426a5b21c0993ee7b14","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Status:** Draft\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nEnhance the `MetadataService` and related data models to support improved metadata validation, persistence, and manipulation capabilities for the AgentCube CLI.\n\n---\n\n## Base References\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — Lines 245-256 (MetadataService class), 324-351 (AgentMetadata model), 353-374 (MetadataOptions dataclass)\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Lines 534-546 (Metadata file format), 522-533 (Workspace validation)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Enhanced metadata validation\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive validation for metadata fields beyond basic type checking.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate agent name format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `agent_name` containing invalid characters (e.g., spaces, uppercase letters, special chars)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_agent_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate that the name follows DNS-1123 subdomain format (lowercase alphanumeric, hyphens allowed between characters, max 63 chars)\n- **AND** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` with a descriptive message when validation fails\n\n#### Scenario: Validate entrypoint format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `entrypoint` field\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify the entrypoint is a valid command string for the specified language\n- **AND** for Python, the system SHALL check it starts with `python` or `python3`\n- **AND** for Java, the system SHALL check it references a valid Java class or JAR execution pattern\n\n#### Scenario: Validate image URL format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `image` field containing `url`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_image_url` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the URL follows container image registry format (e.g., `registry.io/namespace/name:tag`)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate port range with context\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `port` field\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_port` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate port is in range 1-65535\n- **AND** the system SHALL warn if port is below 1024 (privileged ports require special permissions)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata migration and versioning\nThe system SHALL support metadata schema versioning and automatic migration.\n\n#### Scenario: Detect metadata schema version\n- **GIVEN** an existing `agent_metadata.yaml` file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read the `schema_version` field if present\n- **AND** the system SHALL default to version `\"1.0.0\"` if not present\n\n#### Scenario: Migrate from legacy format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file from a previous CLI version with `schema_version < \"1.0.0\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL apply automatic migrations to convert to current schema\n- **AND** the system SHALL preserve all valid fields while mapping deprecated field names to new ones\n- **AND** the system SHALL save the migrated metadata with updated `schema_version`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate schema compatibility\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version` newer than supported version\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SchemaVersionError` indicating the CLI needs to be upgraded\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata merge and override\nThe system SHALL provide robust merge capabilities for combining metadata sources.\n\n#### Scenario: Merge metadata with CLI options\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata from file and CLI options (e.g., `--agent-name`, `--port`)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called with `MetadataOptions` and existing `AgentMetadata`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL apply CLI overrides to the metadata\n- **AND** the system SHALL preserve fields not specified in CLI options\n- **AND** the system SHALL track which fields were overridden for logging\n\n#### Scenario: Merge with validation\n- **GIVEN** metadata that conflicts when merged (e.g., language mismatch between file and CLI)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the merged result\n- **AND** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` if the merged metadata is invalid\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata templates and presets\nThe system SHALL support metadata templates for common agent patterns.\n\n#### Scenario: Load template\n- **GIVEN** a template name (e.g., `\"python-fastapi\"`, `\"java-spring\"`)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the template configuration from a built-in or user-defined template directory\n- **AND** the system SHALL return an `AgentMetadata` object with template defaults\n\n#### Scenario: Validate template completeness\n- **GIVEN** a user-defined template file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify the template contains all required fields\n- **AND** the system SHALL warn about optional fields that should be provided by the user\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata validation for deployment\nThe system SHALL validate metadata requirements before deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate for AgentCube deployment\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` are present\n- **AND** the system SHALL verify `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` are set\n- **AND** the system SHALL raise `DeploymentValidationError` if required fields are missing\n\n#### Scenario: Validate for Kubernetes deployment\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify `image` field contains valid `url` and `tag`\n- **AND** the system SHALL verify `port` is set and valid\n- **AND** the system SHALL verify `namespace` is set if provided in metadata\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata serialization and deserialization\nThe system SHALL support multiple serialization formats with consistent behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: Serialize to YAML with comments\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write YAML with helpful comments for each field\n- **AND** the system SHALL exclude fields with `None` values\n- **AND** the system SHALL preserve field order from the model definition\n\n#### Scenario: Deserialize with environment variable expansion\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file containing environment variable references (e.g., `${REGISTRY_URL}`)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL expand environment variables in string fields\n- **AND** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` if a required environment variable is not set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata history and rollback\nThe system SHALL track metadata changes and support rollback.\n\n#### Scenario: Track metadata changes\n- **GIVEN** a workspace with existing metadata\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a backup of the previous metadata file\n- **AND** the system SHALL store the backup in a `.agentcube/metadata_history/` directory\n- **AND** the backup filename SHALL include a timestamp (e.g., `agent_metadata_20250411_120000.yaml`)\n\n#### Scenario: Rollback to previous version\n- **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.rollback_metadata` is called with a version identifier\n- **THEN** the system SHALL restore the specified backup to the main metadata file\n- **AND** the system SHALL create a backup of the current metadata before rolling back\n\n#### Scenario: List metadata history\n- **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.list_metadata_history` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a list of available backups with timestamps\n- **AND** the system SHALL indicate which backup is currently active\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata validation for security\nThe system SHALL validate metadata for security best practices.\n\n#### Scenario: Detect credentials in metadata\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL scan for potential credentials in all string fields\n- **AND** the system SHALL warn if patterns resembling API keys, passwords, or tokens are found\n- **AND** the system SHALL recommend using environment variables instead\n\n#### Scenario: Validate registry credentials\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `registry_username` and `registry_password`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_registry_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL check if credentials are present when `registry_url` requires authentication\n- **AND** the system SHALL warn about storing credentials in plaintext metadata\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Changes\n\n### `AgentMetadata` enhancements\n\nAdd new fields to `AgentMetadata`:\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `schema_version` | `str` | `\"1.0.0\"` | Metadata schema version for migration support |\n| `template_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Name of template used to create this metadata |\n| `metadata_created_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp when metadata was first created |\n| `metadata_updated_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp of last metadata update |\n| `deployment_history` | `Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]]` | `None` | Track deployment attempts and results |\n\nAdd new validators:\n- `validate_agent_name_format` - DNS-1123 subdomain format\n- `validate_entrypoint_command` - Language-specific command validation\n- `validate_registry_url` - Container registry URL format\n\n### `MetadataService` new methods\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def validate_agent_name(self, agent_name: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_entrypoint(self, entrypoint: str, language: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_image_url(self, image_url: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_port_context(self, port: int) -> None: ...\n    def get_schema_version(self, workspace_path: Path) -> str: ...\n    def migrate_metadata(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, from_version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def merge_metadata(self, base: AgentMetadata, overrides: MetadataOptions) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def load_template(self, template_name: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def validate_template(self, template_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def validate_for_deployment(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, provider: str) -> None: ...\n    def expand_env_vars(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def backup_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Path: ...\n    def rollback_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def list_metadata_history(self, workspace_path: Path) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n    def scan_for_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> List[str]: ...\n    def validate_registry_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### New exceptions\n\n```python\nclass MetadataValidationError(ValidationError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata validation fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass SchemaVersionError(ValueError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata schema version is incompatible\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DeploymentValidationError(MetadataValidationError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata is invalid for deployment\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass TemplateNotFoundError(FileNotFoundError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a requested template is not found\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit tests for `MetadataService`\n\n- Test all validation methods with valid and invalid inputs\n- Test metadata merge logic with various override scenarios\n- Test template loading and validation\n- Test schema migration between versions\n- Test backup and rollback functionality\n- Test environment variable expansion\n\n### Integration tests\n\n- Test end-to-end metadata persistence and loading\n- Test metadata validation in the context of `pack` command\n- Test deployment validation in the context of `publish` command\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Backwards compatibility**: The system MUST maintain compatibility with existing metadata files from previous CLI versions\n2. **Performance**: Metadata operations should complete within 100ms for typical workspaces\n3. **Security**: Credentials scanning should use pattern matching but not attempt to validate actual credentials\n4. **Extensibility**: Template system should support both built-in and user-defined templates\n5. **History limit**: Keep maximum 10 metadata backups by default, configurable via environment variable\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\nNo new external dependencies required. Use existing:\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` for validation and serialization\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML I/O\n- `python-dotenv` (optional) for enhanced environment variable support\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. All validation scenarios pass with appropriate error messages\n2. Metadata migration works for at least 2 previous schema versions\n3. Template system supports at least 3 built-in templates\n4. Metadata history tracks at least 10 changes with rollback capability\n5. Security scanning detects common credential patterns\n6. All new methods have test coverage >= 90%","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775872062798,"end":1775872062804}}}}
