{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775872067142,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a394644001l4ZpItoZpd2Wzg","messageID":"msg_d7a394279001DqSNN8QdTW03I9","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872068154,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a394a17001Kv1NQAE2gDuYCT","messageID":"msg_d7a394279001DqSNN8QdTW03I9","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d7aa831687134fc2be8dbf8c8b5c21cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status Commands\n2: \n3: ## Module: `cmd/cli`\n4: \n5: ## Language: Python\n6: \n7: ## Size: M\n8: \n9: ## Delta Overview\n10: \n11: Add the `invoke` and `status` commands to the AgentCube CLI for sending payloads to deployed agents and checking their deployment status, supporting both AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## REQ-001: Invoke command initialization\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Invoke command registration and default options\n18: \n19: System SHALL provide an `invoke` command that sends JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints with configurable options.\n20: \n21: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n22: - Command name: `invoke`\n23: - Supports workspace path specification\n24: - Supports JSON payload specification\n25: - Supports custom HTTP headers\n26: - Supports provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n27: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n28: \n29: **Scenarios:**\n30: \n31: #### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\n32: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n33: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke` without options\n34: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n35:   - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n36:   - `payload`: `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n37:   - `header_list`: `None`\n38:   - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n39:   - `verbose`: `False`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\n42: - **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\n43: - **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--payload`, `--header`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n44: - **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\n45:   - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\n46:   - `payload`: JSON-formatted string\n47:   - `header_list`: list of strings in \"key:value\" format\n48:   - `provider`: string (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n49:   - `verbose`: boolean flag\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## REQ-002: Payload validation and parsing\n54: \n55: ### Requirement: JSON payload validation\n56: \n57: System SHALL validate the payload format before invocation and provide clear error messages.\n58: \n59: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n60: - Validates JSON syntax before sending\n61: - Rejects invalid JSON with clear error message\n62: - Supports complex nested JSON structures\n63: - Exits with code 1 on invalid payload\n64: \n65: **Scenarios:**\n66: \n67: #### Scenario 2.1: Valid JSON payload\n68: - **GIVEN** the user provides a valid JSON payload string\n69: - **WHEN** `--payload '{\"query\": \"What is AI?\", \"context\": [\"ML\"]}'` is parsed\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n71:   - Successfully parse it into a Python dictionary\n72:   - Pass it to the runtime\n73:   - Continue with invocation\n74: \n75: #### Scenario 2.2: Invalid JSON payload\n76: - **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid JSON payload\n77: - **WHEN** `--payload '{invalid json}'` is parsed\n78: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n79:   - Print \"Invalid JSON payload\" in red\n80:   - Exit with code `1`\n81:   - NOT call `InvokeRuntime.invoke` or `_handle_error`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario 2.3: Empty payload default\n84: - **GIVEN** the user omits the `--payload` option\n85: - **WHEN** the command runs with default payload `\"{}\"`\n86: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n87:   - Parse `\"{}\"` as an empty dictionary\n88:   - Pass empty dictionary to runtime\n89: \n90: #### Scenario 2.4: Complex nested payload\n91: - **GIVEN** the user provides a complex nested JSON structure\n92: - **WHEN** `--payload '{\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}], \"temperature\": 0.7, \"max_tokens\": 100}'` is parsed\n93: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n94:   - Preserve the full structure\n95:   - Pass it to the runtime\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## REQ-003: Header format validation\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: Custom header validation\n102: \n103: System SHALL validate custom header format and provide clear error messages for malformed headers.\n104: \n105: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n106: - Validates header format contains at least one colon\n107: - Rejects invalid format with clear error message\n108: - Supports headers with colons in values\n109: - Supports multiple header specifications\n110: \n111: **Scenarios:**\n112: \n113: #### Scenario 3.1: Valid header format\n114: - **GIVEN** the user provides correctly formatted headers\n115: - **WHEN** parsing `--header 'Authorization: Bearer token'` and `--header 'Content-Type: application/json'`\n116: - **THEN** each header SHALL be:\n117:   - Split at the first `:` into key and value\n118: \n119: #### Scenario 3.2: Invalid header without colon\n120: - **GIVEN** the user provides a header string without a colon separator\n121: - **WHEN** `--header 'InvalidHeader'` is parsed\n122: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n123:   - Print \"Header must be in 'key:value' format\" in red\n124:   - Exit with code `1`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario 3.3: Header with multiple colons\n127: - **GIVEN** the user provides a header with colons in the value\n128: - **WHEN** `--header 'Authorization: Bearer:token:with:colons'` is parsed\n129: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n130:   - Split only at the first `:`\n131:   - key = `\"Authorization\"`\n132:   - value = `\"Bearer:token:with:colons\"`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario 3.4: Empty header value\n135: - **GIVEN** the user provides a header with an empty value\n136: - **WHEN** `--header 'X-Custom-Header:'` is parsed\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n138:   - key = `\"X-Custom-Header\"`\n139:   - value = `\"\"` (empty string)\n140: \n141: #### Scenario 3.5: Multiple header specifications\n142: - **GIVEN** the user needs to pass multiple custom headers\n143: - **WHEN** the command is `invoke --header 'Authorization: Bearer token1' --header 'X-Custom-Header: value'`\n144: - **THEN** `header_list` SHALL be `['Authorization: Bearer token1', 'X-Custom-Header: value']`\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## REQ-004: Session header management\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Automatic session ID header injection\n151: \n152: System SHALL automatically add the session ID header when metadata contains a `session_id`.\n153: \n154: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n155: - Automatically adds session header when session_id exists\n156: - Does not add session header when session_id is missing\n157: - Allows custom header to override metadata session_id\n158: - Uses correct header name spelling\n159: \n160: **Scenarios:**\n161: \n162: #### Scenario 4.1: Session ID from metadata\n163: - **GIVEN** the agent metadata contains `session_id: \"abc-123-def\"`\n164: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with this metadata\n165: - **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include:\n166:   - Header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc-123-def`\n167: \n168: #### Scenario 4.2: No session ID in metadata\n169: - **GIVEN** the agent metadata does not contain a `session_id` field\n170: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n171: - **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL NOT include:\n172:   - The session header\n173: \n174: #### Scenario 4.3: Session ID override with custom header\n175: - **GIVEN** the metadata has `session_id: \"abc-123\"`\n176: - **WHEN** the user provides `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: custom-session'`\n177: - **THEN** the custom header value SHALL:\n178:   - Take precedence over the metadata session ID\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ## REQ-005: Workspace path resolution\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Path resolution for invoke\n185: \n186: System SHALL resolve the workspace path relative to the current working directory.\n187: \n188: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n189: - Resolves relative paths correctly\n190: - Handles absolute paths correctly\n191: - Uses current directory as default\n192: \n193: **Scenarios:**\n194: \n195: #### Scenario 5.1: Relative workspace path\n196: - **GIVEN** the user provides `-f ./my-agent`\n197: - **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL be:\n199:   - Resolved to `{cwd}/my-agent`\n200: \n201: #### Scenario 5.2: Absolute workspace path\n202: - **GIVEN** the user provides `-f /absolute/path/to/agent`\n203: - **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL remain:\n205:   - `/absolute/path/to/agent`\n206: \n207: #### Scenario 5.3: Default workspace path\n208: - **GIVEN** the user omits the `-f` option\n209: - **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n210: - **THEN** it SHALL be:\n211:   - The current working directory `\".\"`\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## REQ-006: Provider-specific invocation\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: Provider-based routing\n218: \n219: System SHALL route invocation requests to the appropriate endpoint based on the `provider` parameter.\n220: \n221: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n222: - Routes to AgentRuntime CR endpoint for agentcube provider\n223: - Routes to K8s service endpoint for k8s provider\n224: - Rewrites URL correctly for AgentRuntime invocations\n225: - Uses Router URL when available\n226: \n227: **Scenarios:**\n228: \n229: #### Scenario 6.1: AgentCube provider (default)\n230: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n231: - **WHEN** the agent is deployed as an AgentRuntime CR\n232: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n233:   - Load metadata and check for `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n234:   - Rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n235:   - Include session headers if present\n236: \n237: #### Scenario 6.2: Kubernetes provider\n238: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n239: - **WHEN** the agent is deployed as a standard K8s Deployment/Service\n240: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n241:   - Use the service URL from metadata (e.g., `http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n242:   - NOT rewrite the URL to the AgentRuntime invocation path\n243:   - Direct POST to the agent's endpoint\n244: \n245: #### Scenario 6.3: AgentCube provider with Router URL\n246: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n247: - **WHEN** metadata contains `router_url`\n248: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n249:   - Use the Router URL for invocation\n250:   - Format as `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## REQ-007: Invoke prerequisites validation\n255: \n256: ### Requirement: Pre-invocation validation\n257: \n258: System SHALL validate that all prerequisites are met before attempting invocation.\n259: \n260: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n261: - Validates agent is published (has agent_id)\n262: - Validates metadata file exists\n263: - Validates workspace path exists\n264: - Validates provider value is valid\n265: \n266: **Scenarios:**\n267: \n268: #### Scenario 7.1: Agent not published\n269: - **GIVEN** the workspace metadata lacks `agent_id`\n270: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n271: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n272:   - Raise an error indicating the agent must be published first\n273: \n274: #### Scenario 7.2: Missing metadata file\n275: - **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n276: - **WHEN** it has no `agent_metadata.yaml` (or fallbacks)\n277: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n278:   - Raise an error indicating metadata file is missing\n279: \n280: #### Scenario 7.3: Invalid workspace path\n281: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n282: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n283: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n284:   - Raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n285: \n286: #### Scenario 7.4: Invalid provider value\n287: - **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid provider value\n288: - **WHEN** `--provider invalid-provider` is parsed\n289: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n290:   - Validate and reject the provider value\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## REQ-008: Invoke response handling\n295: \n296: ### Requirement: Response processing and display\n297: \n298: System SHALL handle and display invocation responses appropriately.\n299: \n300: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n301: - Displays successful responses in readable format\n302: - Displays error responses with details\n303: - Handles network timeouts gracefully\n304: - Formats JSON responses properly\n305: \n306: **Scenarios:**\n307: \n308: #### Scenario 8.1: Successful invocation\n309: - **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns a successful response (2xx)\n310: - **WHEN** the invocation completes\n311: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n312:   - Print the response in a formatted manner\n313: \n314: #### Scenario 8.2: Agent returns error response\n315: - **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns an error response (4xx or 5xx)\n316: - **WHEN** the invocation completes\n317: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n318:   - Display the error message\n319:   - Display response details\n320: \n321: #### Scenario 8.3: Network timeout\n322: - **GIVEN** the invocation request times out\n323: - **WHEN** the timeout period elapses\n324: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n325:   - Raise a timeout exception\n326:   - Handle exception via `_handle_error`\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## REQ-009: Error handling for invoke\n331: \n332: ### Requirement: Consistent error handling\n333: \n334: System SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n335: \n336: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n337: - Catches runtime exceptions\n338: - Displays error messages in red\n339: - Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n340: - Exits with code 1 on errors\n341: \n342: **Scenarios:**\n343: \n344: #### Scenario 9.1: Runtime exception\n345: - **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` raises a `RuntimeError`\n346: - **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n347: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n348:   - Print \"Error invoke: {error_message}\" in red\n349:   - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n350:   - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n351: \n352: #### Scenario 9.2: HTTP connection error\n353: - **GIVEN** there is a network connectivity issue\n354: - **WHEN** the invocation attempt fails\n355: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n356:   - Catch the connection error\n357:   - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n358: \n359: #### Scenario 9.3: Subcommand verbose logging\n360: - **GIVEN** the user uses the local `--verbose` flag on the `invoke` command\n361: - **WHEN** an error occurs\n362: - **THEN** the traceback SHALL be:\n363:   - Printed even if the global `-v` was not passed\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ## REQ-010: Status command initialization\n368: \n369: ### Requirement: Status command registration and default options\n370: \n371: System SHALL provide a `status` command that displays the current state of a deployed agent.\n372: \n373: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n374: - Command name: `status`\n375: - Supports workspace path specification\n376: - Supports provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n377: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n378: - Displays status in formatted table\n379: \n380: **Scenarios:**\n381: \n382: #### Scenario 10.1: Command registration and default options\n383: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n384: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube status` without options\n385: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n386:   - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n387:   - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n388:   - `verbose`: `False`\n389: \n390: #### Scenario 10.2: Custom workspace and provider\n391: - **GIVEN** the user specifies custom options\n392: - **WHEN** parsing `status -f /path/to/workspace --provider k8s`\n393: - **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n394:   - `workspace`: `\"/path/to/workspace\"`\n395:   - `provider`: `\"k8s\"`\n396:   - `verbose`: `False`\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## REQ-011: Status display formatting\n401: \n402: ### Requirement: Rich table formatting\n403: \n404: System SHALL display agent status in a Rich `Table` with clear, readable formatting.\n405: \n406: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n407: - Displays status in Rich table\n408: - Shows key information fields\n409: - Handles missing fields gracefully\n410: - Provides clear status indication\n411: \n412: **Scenarios:**\n413: \n414: #### Scenario 11.1: Successful status retrieval\n415: - **GIVEN** the agent is successfully deployed and status is available\n416: - **WHEN** `status` runs and retrieves status information\n417: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n418:   - A Rich `Table` containing:\n419:     - Field names in the first column\n420:     - Field values in the second column\n421:     - Key information: agent name, namespace, status, endpoint, deployment details\n422: \n423: #### Scenario 11.2: Status table fields\n424: - **GIVEN** the agent status is retrieved\n425: - **WHEN** the Rich table is rendered\n426: - **THEN** it SHALL include these fields when available:\n427:   - Agent Name\n428:   - Namespace\n429:   - Status (e.g., \"running\", \"ready\", \"error\", \"not_published\")\n430:   - Agent Endpoint\n431:   - Session ID (if applicable)\n432:   - Deployment Type (AgentRuntime or Deployment/Service)\n433:   - Image URL\n434:   - Version\n435: \n436: #### Scenario 11.3: Status not published\n437: - **GIVEN** the agent metadata has no `agent_id` field\n438: - **WHEN** `status` is called and returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n439: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n440:   - Print a message indicating the agent is not published\n441:   - Provide guidance to run `publish` command first\n442:   - Exit with code `1`\n443: \n444: ---\n445: \n446: ## REQ-012: Status for AgentCube provider\n447: \n448: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CR status retrieval\n449: \n450: System SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the AgentCube provider.\n451: \n452: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n453: - Retrieves status from AgentRuntime CR\n454: - Handles CR with status field\n455: - Handles CR without status field\n456: - Handles CR not found\n457: \n458: **Scenarios:**\n459: \n460: #### Scenario 12.1: AgentRuntime CR with status\n461: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n462: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists with status\n463: - **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n464:   - Read status from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present\n465:   - Extract `status` and `agentEndpoint` from the CR status\n466: \n467: #### Scenario 12.2: AgentRuntime CR created but no status\n468: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n469: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field\n470: - **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n471:   - Return status `\"created_no_status\"`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario 12.3: AgentRuntime CR not found\n474: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n475: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n476: - **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n477:   - Return status `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n478: \n479: #### Scenario 12.4: AgentRuntime CR error status\n480: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR status indicates an error condition\n481: - **WHEN** status is retrieved\n482: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n483:   - Display error details\n484:   - Exit with code `1`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## REQ-013: Status for Kubernetes provider\n489: \n490: ### Requirement: K8s Deployment/Service status retrieval\n491: \n492: System SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the standard Kubernetes provider.\n493: \n494: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n495: - Queries both Deployment and Service status\n496: - Displays deployment ready replicas\n497: - Displays service node port and URL\n498: - Handles resources not found\n499: \n500: **Scenarios:**\n501: \n502: #### Scenario 13.1: K8s deployment and service status\n503: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n504: - **WHEN** the agent is deployed with Deployment and Service\n505: - **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` SHALL:\n506:   - Query both Deployment and Service status\n507:   - Include:\n508:     - Deployment ready replicas\n509:     - Service node port\n510:     - Service URL\n511:     - Pod status summary\n512: \n513: #### Scenario 13.2: K8s deployment not ready\n514: - **GIVEN** the Deployment exists but replicas are not ready\n515: - **WHEN** status is retrieved\n516: - **THEN** the status SHALL indicate:\n517:   - `\"not_ready\"` with details about current vs. desired replicas\n518: \n519: #### Scenario 13.3: K8s resources not found\n520: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n521: - **WHEN** neither Deployment nor Service exists\n522: - **THEN** the status SHALL indicate:\n523:   - `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n524: \n525: ---\n526: \n527: ## REQ-014: Status exit codes\n528: \n529: ### Requirement: Appropriate exit codes\n530: \n531: System SHALL use appropriate exit codes to indicate the result of status checks.\n532: \n533: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n534: - Exit code 0 for success/ready\n535: - Exit code 1 for failure/not-ready/not-published\n536: \n537: **Scenarios:**\n538: \n539: #### Scenario 14.1: Successful status (agent running)\n540: - **GIVEN** the agent status indicates it is running or ready\n541: - **WHEN** `status` completes\n542: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n543:   - code `0`\n544: \n545: #### Scenario 14.2: Agent not published\n546: - **GIVEN** the agent has no `agent_id` in metadata\n547: - **WHEN** `status` completes\n548: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n549:   - code `1`\n550: \n551: #### Scenario 14.3: Agent in error state\n552: - **GIVEN** the agent status indicates an error condition\n553: - **WHEN** `status` completes\n554: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n555:   - code `1`\n556: \n557: #### Scenario 14.4: Agent not found in Kubernetes\n558: - **GIVEN** the agent was previously published but the CR or Deployment no longer exists\n559: - **WHEN** `status` completes\n560: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n561:   - code `1`\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## REQ-015: Workspace path resolution for status\n566: \n567: ### Requirement: Path resolution for status\n568: \n569: System SHALL resolve the workspace path for status checks.\n570: \n571: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n572: - Uses current directory as default\n573: - Resolves custom paths correctly\n574: - Validates path existence\n575: \n576: **Scenarios:**\n577: \n578: #### Scenario 15.1: Default workspace\n579: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status` without `-f` option\n580: - **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n581: - **THEN** it SHALL use:\n582:   - The current working directory `\".\"`\n583: \n584: #### Scenario 15.2: Custom workspace path\n585: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status -f /path/to/agent`\n586: - **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n587: - **THEN** it SHALL use:\n588:   - `/path/to/agent`\n589: \n590: #### Scenario 15.3: Missing workspace\n591: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n592: - **WHEN** `status` is called\n593: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n594:   - Raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## REQ-016: Verbose logging for status\n599: \n600: ### Requirement: Detailed logging support\n601: \n602: System SHALL provide detailed logging when verbose mode is enabled.\n603: \n604: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n605: - Logs Kubernetes API calls\n606: - Logs resource retrieval\n607: - Logs status parsing\n608: - Logs warnings and additional information\n609: \n610: **Scenarios:**\n611: \n612: #### Scenario 16.1: Verbose status output\n613: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status --verbose`\n614: - **WHEN** status is retrieved\n615: - **THEN** the system SHALL log:\n616:   - Additional details about Kubernetes API calls\n617:   - CR or resource retrieval\n618:   - Status parsing\n619:   - Any warnings or additional information\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## REQ-017: Error handling for status\n624: \n625: ### Requirement: Consistent error handling\n626: \n627: System SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n628: \n629: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n630: - Catches runtime exceptions\n631: - Displays error messages in red\n632: - Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n633: - Exits with code 1 on errors\n634: \n635: **Scenarios:**\n636: \n637: #### Scenario 17.1: Status retrieval exception\n638: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` raises a `RuntimeError`\n639: - **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n640: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n641:   - Print \"Error status: {error_message}\" in red\n642:   - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n643:   - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n644: \n645: #### Scenario 17.2: Kubernetes connection error\n646: - **GIVEN** there is an issue connecting to the Kubernetes API\n647: - **WHEN** `status` attempts to query the cluster\n648: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n649:   - Catch the connection error\n650:   - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n651: \n652: #### Scenario 17.3: Metadata validation error\n653: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but contains invalid data\n654: - **WHEN** `status` attempts to load metadata\n655: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n656:   - Catch the validation error\n657:   - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n658: \n659: ---\n660: \n661: ## REQ-018: Metadata file loading\n662: \n663: ### Requirement: Metadata loading with fallback\n664: \n665: System SHALL load agent metadata from the workspace with appropriate fallback behavior.\n666: \n667: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n668: - Loads from agent_metadata.yaml first\n669: - Falls back to agent.yaml\n670: - Falls back to metadata.yaml\n671: - Raises error if none found\n672: \n673: **Scenarios:**\n674: \n675: #### Scenario 18.1: Primary metadata file exists\n676: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n677: - **WHEN** metadata is loaded for `invoke` or `status`\n678: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n679:   - Load from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n680: \n681: #### Scenario 18.2: Primary missing, first fallback\n682: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist\n683: - **WHEN** `agent.yaml` does exist\n684: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n685:   - Load from `agent.yaml`\n686: \n687: #### Scenario 18.3: Primary and first fallback missing\n688: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists\n689: - **WHEN** `metadata.yaml` does exist\n690: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n691:   - Load from `metadata.yaml`\n692: \n693: #### Scenario 18.4: No metadata file found\n694: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n695: - **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n696: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n697:   - Raise an error indicating no metadata file was found\n698: \n699: ---\n700: \n701: ## REQ-019: Global verbose logging propagation\n702: \n703: ### Requirement: Verbose flag propagation\n704: \n705: System SHALL correctly propagate verbose logging settings from the root callback to subcommands.\n706: \n707: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n708: - Global verbose enables logging for all subcommands\n709: - Subcommand verbose enables logging for that subcommand\n710: - Combination of both works correctly\n711: \n712: **Scenarios:**\n713: \n714: #### Scenario 19.1: Global verbose with subcommand verbose\n715: - **GIVEN** the user passes both global `-v` and local `--verbose` on `invoke` or `status`\n716: - **WHEN** the command runs\n717: - **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n718:   - Enabled\n719: \n720: #### Scenario 19.2: Subcommand verbose without global verbose\n721: - **GIVEN** the user passes only `invoke --verbose` without global `-v`\n722: - **WHEN** the command runs\n723: - **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n724:   - Enabled for that subcommand\n725: \n726: #### Scenario 19.3: Global verbose without subcommand verbose\n727: - **GIVEN** the user passes only global `-v` without subcommand `--verbose`\n728: - **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` runs\n729: - **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n730:   - Enabled\n731: \n732: ---\n733: \n734: ## REQ-020: Rich output formatting\n735: \n736: ### Requirement: Consistent Rich library usage\n737: \n738: System SHALL use Rich library for consistent, readable command output.\n739: \n740: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n741: - Uses Rich table for status\n742: - Uses Rich console for errors\n743: - Uses Rich progress spinner for long operations\n744: \n745: **Scenarios:**\n746: \n747: #### Scenario 20.1: Rich table for status\n748: - **GIVEN** status information is available\n749: - **WHEN** displaying status\n750: - **THEN** the output SHALL be:\n751:   - Formatted as a Rich table with proper styling\n752: \n753: #### Scenario 20.2: Rich console for errors\n754: - **GIVEN** an error occurs\n755: - **WHEN** the error is displayed\n756: - **THEN** error messages SHALL use:\n757:   - Rich console for red-colored output\n758: \n759: #### Scenario 20.3: Rich progress spinner\n760: - **GIVEN** a long-running operation\n761: - **WHEN** the operation is in progress\n762: - **THEN** the system SHALL display:\n763:   - A Rich Progress spinner\n764: \n765: ---\n766: \n767: ## Integration Scenarios\n768: \n769: ### INT-001: Full workflow - pack, build, publish, invoke\n770: \n771: #### Scenario INT-1.1: Complete lifecycle\n772: - **GIVEN** a valid agent workspace\n773: - **WHEN** the user runs:\n774:   1. `pack` - successfully packages the workspace\n775:   2. `build` - successfully builds the image\n776:   3. `publish --provider agentcube` - successfully deploys to Kubernetes\n777:   4. `invoke --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}'` - sends a payload\n778: - **THEN** each command SHALL:\n779:   - Complete successfully\n780:   - `invoke` SHALL receive a response from the deployed agent\n781: \n782: #### Scenario INT-1.2: Invoke after local build publish\n783: - **GIVEN** an agent built in local mode\n784: - **WHEN** published with `--image-url` and `--provider k8s`\n785: - **THEN** `invoke --provider k8s` SHALL:\n786:   - Successfully send requests to the NodePort service\n787: \n788: ### INT-002: Status checks during deployment lifecycle\n789: \n790: #### Scenario INT-2.1: Status before publish\n791: - **GIVEN** an agent has been packed but not published\n792: - **WHEN** `status` is run\n793: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n794:   - Indicate the agent is not published\n795:   - Exit with code `1`\n796: \n797: #### Scenario INT-2.2: Status during deployment rollout\n798: - **GIVEN** an agent has been published and is in the process of becoming ready\n799: - **WHEN** `status` is run\n800: - **THEN** the system SHALL show:\n801:   - The current deployment state (e.g., \"not_ready\")\n802: \n803: #### Scenario INT-2.3: Status after agent is ready\n804: - **GIVEN** an agent deployment has completed successfully\n805: - **WHEN** `status` is run\n806: - **THEN** the system SHALL show:\n807:   - Status \"ready\" or \"running\" with full endpoint information\n808: \n809: ### INT-003: Session management across invokes\n810: \n811: #### Scenario INT-3.1: Reuse session ID from metadata\n812: - **GIVEN** the first `invoke` establishes a session\n813: - **WHEN** it saves `session_id` to metadata\n814: - **THEN** subsequent `invoke` commands SHALL:\n815:   - Use the existing `session_id` from metadata\n816: \n817: #### Scenario INT-3.2: Session ID in headers\n818: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id: \"existing-session\"`\n819: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called with `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: new-session'`\n820: - **THEN** the custom header SHALL:\n821:   - Override the metadata session ID for that specific request\n822: \n823: ---\n824: \n825: ## Edge Cases and Error Conditions\n826: \n827: ### EDGE-001: Malformed metadata\n828: \n829: #### Scenario EDGE-1.1: Missing required fields\n830: - **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields\n831: - **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` attempts to load metadata\n832: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n833:   - Raise a validation error indicating which fields are missing\n834: \n835: #### Scenario EDGE-1.2: Invalid data types in metadata\n836: - **GIVEN** the metadata file contains fields with invalid data types\n837: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n838: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n839:   - Raise a validation error with details about the type mismatch\n840: \n841: ### EDGE-002: Concurrent invocations\n842: \n843: #### Scenario EDGE-2.1: Multiple invocations in parallel\n844: - **GIVEN** an agent is deployed and ready\n845: - **WHEN** multiple `invoke` commands are run simultaneously\n846: - **THEN** each invocation SHALL:\n847:   - Receive its own response\n848:   - Have session headers correctly applied to each request\n849: \n850: ### EDGE-003: Large payloads\n851: \n852: #### Scenario EDGE-3.1: Large JSON payload\n853: - **GIVEN** the user provides a large JSON payload (e.g., 1MB)\n854: - **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called with the large payload\n855: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n856:   - Successfully parse and send the payload to the agent endpoint\n857: \n858: #### Scenario EDGE-3.2: Extremely large payload rejection\n859: - **GIVEN** the user provides an extremely large JSON payload exceeding system limits\n860: - **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called\n861: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n862:   - Reject the payload with an appropriate error message\n863: \n864: ---\n865: \n866: ## Provider-specific Edge Cases\n867: \n868: ### EDGE-004: AgentCube provider edge cases\n869: \n870: #### Scenario EDGE-4.1: Missing router_url\n871: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n872: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n873: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n874:   - Raise an error indicating `router_url` is required for AgentCube provider\n875: \n876: #### Scenario EDGE-4.2: AgentRuntime CR with missing status field\n877: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists\n878: - **WHEN** it has no status field in its spec\n879: - **THEN** `status` SHALL:\n880:   - Handle gracefully and return appropriate status\n881: \n882: ### EDGE-005: Kubernetes provider edge cases\n883: \n884: #### Scenario EDGE-5.1: NodePort outside valid range\n885: - **GIVEN** a K8s deployment was created with an invalid NodePort\n886: - **WHEN** `invoke --provider k8s` attempts to connect\n887: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n888:   - Handle connection errors appropriately\n889: \n890: #### Scenario EDGE-5.2: Service with no endpoints\n891: - **GIVEN** the K8s Service exists\n892: - **WHEN** it has no ready endpoints\n893: - **THEN** `invoke --provider k8s` SHALL:\n894:   - Handle connection errors\n895:   - Provide informative messages\n896: \n897: ---\n898: \n899: ## Technical Constraints\n900: \n901: ### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n902: \n903: System SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n904: \n905: **Dependencies:**\n906: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` for CLI framework\n907: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation\n908: - `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing\n909: - `httpx>=0.24.0` for HTTP client\n910: - `rich>=13.0.0` for formatted console output\n911: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0` for Kubernetes API client (optional)\n912: \n913: ### Requirement: File locations\n914: \n915: - CLI command definition: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n916: - InvokeRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n917: - StatusRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n918: - MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n919: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n920: - Metadata filename: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n921: \n922: ### Requirement: Exit codes\n923: \n924: System SHALL return appropriate exit codes:\n925: - Exit code 0 for successful operations\n926: - Exit code 1 for failures\n927: - Exit code 130 for SIGINT (Ctrl+C) interruption\n928: \n929: ---\n930: \n931: ## Testing Requirements\n932: \n933: ### Unit Test Scenarios\n934: \n935: #### Scenario UT-1.1: Test payload validation\n936: - **GIVEN** a test suite for payload validation\n937: - **WHEN** tests run\n938: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n939:   - Valid JSON payload parsing\n940:   - Invalid JSON payload rejection\n941:   - Empty payload default handling\n942:   - Complex nested payload parsing\n943: \n944: #### Scenario UT-1.2: Test header validation\n945: - **GIVEN** a test suite for header validation\n946: - **WHEN** tests run\n947: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n948:   - Valid header format parsing\n949:   - Invalid header format rejection\n950:   - Multiple headers handling\n951:   - Headers with colons in values\n952:   - Empty header values\n953: \n954: #### Scenario UT-1.3: Test session header management\n955: - **GIVEN** a test suite for session header management\n956: - **WHEN** tests run\n957: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n958:   - Session header injection when session_id exists\n959:   - No session header when session_id is missing\n960:   - Custom header override of session_id\n961: \n962: #### Scenario UT-1.4: Test provider routing\n963: - **GIVEN** a test suite for provider routing\n964: - **WHEN** tests run\n965: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n966:   - AgentCube provider URL rewriting\n967:   - K8s provider direct routing\n968:   - Router URL usage for AgentCube provider\n969: \n970: #### Scenario UT-1.5: Test status retrieval\n971: - **GIVEN** a test suite for status retrieval\n972: - **WHEN** tests run\n973: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n974:   - AgentRuntime CR status retrieval\n975:   - K8s Deployment/Service status retrieval\n976:   - CR not found handling\n977:   - CR without status handling\n978:   - Resources not found handling\n979: \n980: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n981: \n982: #### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end invoke for AgentCube provider\n983: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent with AgentRuntime CR\n984: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n985: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n986:   - Load metadata from workspace\n987:   - Construct correct invocation URL\n988:   - Send payload with proper headers\n989:   - Receive and display response\n990: \n991: #### Scenario IT-1.2: End-to-end invoke for K8s provider\n992: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent with Deployment/Service\n993: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n994: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n995:   - Load metadata from workspace\n996:   - Use service URL for invocation\n997:   - Send payload with proper headers\n998:   - Receive and display response\n999: \n1000: #### Scenario IT-1.3: End-to-end status for AgentCube provider\n1001: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent with AgentRuntime CR\n1002: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube status`\n1003: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n1004:   - Load metadata from workspace\n1005:   - Query AgentRuntime CR\n1006:   - Display status in Rich table\n1007:   - Exit with appropriate code\n1008: \n1009: #### Scenario IT-1.4: End-to-end status for K8s provider\n1010: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent with Deployment/Service\n1011: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s`\n1012: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n1013:   - Load metadata from workspace\n1014:   - Query Deployment and Service\n1015:   - Display status in Rich table\n1016:   - Exit with appropriate code\n1017: \n1018: ### Error Handling Test Scenarios\n1019: \n1020: #### Scenario ET-1.1: Test error propagation for invoke\n1021: - **GIVEN** various error conditions for invoke\n1022: - **WHEN** errors occur during invocation\n1023: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n1024:   - Invalid JSON payload displays error and exits with code 1\n1025:   - Invalid header format displays error and exits with code 1\n1026:   - Agent not published displays error and exits with code 1\n1027:   - Network errors are caught and surfaced\n1028:   - CLI displays error message in red\n1029:   - CLI shows traceback in verbose mode\n1030: \n1031: #### Scenario ET-1.2: Test error propagation for status\n1032: - **GIVEN** various error conditions for status\n1033: - **WHEN** errors occur during status check\n1034: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n1035:   - Agent not published displays guidance and exits with code 1\n1036:   - Kubernetes connection errors are caught and surfaced\n1037:   - Metadata validation errors are caught and surfaced\n1038:   - CLI displays error message in red\n1039:   - CLI shows traceback in verbose mode\n1040: \n1041: ---\n1042: \n1043: ## Acceptance Criteria\n1044: \n1045: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Invoke Command\n1046: \n1047: - [ ] Invoke command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n1048: - [ ] Invalid JSON payloads are rejected with clear error messages\n1049: - [ ] Invalid header formats are rejected with clear error messages\n1050: - [ ] Session headers are automatically added when session_id exists in metadata\n1051: - [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly (relative and absolute)\n1052: - [ ] AgentCube provider routes to AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n1053: - [ ] K8s provider routes directly to service endpoint\n1054: - [ ] Prerequisites are validated before invocation attempts\n1055: - [ ] Successful responses are displayed in a readable format\n1056: - [ ] Error responses and timeouts are handled gracefully\n1057: - [ ] Verbose mode provides detailed logging and traces\n1058: - [ ] Exit code 0 on success, 1 on failure\n1059: \n1060: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Status Command\n1061: \n1062: - [ ] Status command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n1063: - [ ] Status is displayed in a Rich table with clear formatting\n1064: - [ ] \"Not published\" state is detected and reported with guidance\n1065: - [ ] AgentRuntime CR status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n1066: - [ ] K8s Deployment/Service status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n1067: - [ ] Exit code 0 on success/ready, 1 on failure/not-ready/not-published\n1068: - [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly\n1069: - [ ] Verbose mode provides additional debugging information\n1070: - [ ] Errors are caught and surfaced via _handle_error\n1071: \n1072: ### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n1073: \n1074: - [ ] Invoke command completes within reasonable time for typical payloads\n1075: - [ ] Status command completes within reasonable time for typical queries\n1076: - [ ] Memory usage remains reasonable for large payloads\n1077: - [ ] Path traversal protection prevents unauthorized access\n1078: - [ ] Sensitive information in headers is handled securely\n1079: - [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n1080: - [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n1081: - [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end scenarios\n1082: - [ ] Error handling tests verify proper error propagation and display\n1083: \n1084: ---\n1085: \n1086: ## Implementation Notes\n1087: \n1088: ### Key Components\n1089: \n1090: 1. **InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n1091:    - Main runtime class implementing invoke logic\n1092:    - Handles payload validation, header processing, and HTTP requests\n1093:    - Routes to appropriate provider endpoints\n1094: \n1095: 2. **StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n1096:    - Main runtime class implementing status logic\n1097:    - Handles AgentRuntime CR and K8s resource queries\n1098:    - Formats status output for display\n1099: \n1100: 3. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n1101:    - Handles metadata loading and saving\n1102:    - Provides validation methods for metadata fields\n1103: \n1104: 4. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n1105:    - Pydantic model for metadata validation\n1106:    - Contains all agent configuration fields\n1107: \n1108: 5. **Typer CLI framework**\n1109:    - Provides command-line interface definition\n1110:    - Handles option parsing and validation\n1111: \n1112: 6. **Rich library**\n1113:    - Provides formatted console output\n1114:    - Supports tables, progress spinners, and colored text\n1115: \n1116: ### Key Algorithms\n1117: \n1118: #### Invoke Algorithm\n1119: 1. Load metadata from workspace\n1120: 2. Validate agent is published (has agent_id)\n1121: 3. Parse JSON payload (validate syntax)\n1122: 4. Parse custom headers (validate format)\n1123: 5. Determine provider (agentcube or k8s)\n1124: 6. Construct invocation URL based on provider\n1125: 7. Add session header if session_id exists in metadata\n1126: 8. Send HTTP POST request with payload and headers\n1127: 9. Handle response or error\n1128: 10. Display result or error message\n1129: \n1130: #### Status Algorithm\n1131: 1. Load metadata from workspace\n1132: 2. Check if agent is published (has agent_id)\n1133: 3. Determine provider (agentcube or k8s)\n1134: 4. For agentcube provider:\n1135:    - Query AgentRuntime CR\n1136:    - Extract status and endpoint from CR\n1137: 5. For k8s provider:\n1138:    - Query Deployment and Service\n1139:    - Extract deployment and service status\n1140: 6. Format status information in Rich table\n1141: 7. Display table to user\n1142: 8. Exit with appropriate code\n1143: \n1144: #### Header Parsing Algorithm\n1145: 1. For each header string in header_list:\n1146:    - Split at first `:` to get key and value\n1147:    - Validate split produced exactly 2 parts\n1148:    - If not, raise error with format message\n1149: 2. Return dictionary of key-value pairs\n1150: \n1151: #### Session Header Injection Algorithm\n1152: 1. Check if metadata.session_id exists and is truthy\n1153: 2. If yes, add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}`\n1154: 3. Check if custom headers already contain this header\n1155: 4. If custom headers exist, they take precedence\n1156: 5. Return final headers dictionary\n1157: \n1158: ---\n1159: \n1160: ## Related Requirements\n1161: \n1162: - **AR-020:** CLI pack command (required before invoke/status)\n1163: - **AR-021:** CLI build command (required before invoke/status)\n1164: - **AR-022:** CLI publish command (required before invoke/status)\n1165: - **AR-024:** CLI additional commands (future work)\n1166: - **cli-toolkit/spec.md:** Base CLI specifications\n1167: - **deployment/client-go.md:** Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime CR\n1168: - **python-sdk/spec.md:** SDK requirements and HTTP contracts\n\n(End of file - total 1168 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status Commands\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nAdd the `invoke` and `status` commands to the AgentCube CLI for sending payloads to deployed agents and checking their deployment status, supporting both AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Invoke command initialization\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command registration and default options\n\nSystem SHALL provide an `invoke` command that sends JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints with configurable options.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872068142,"end":1775872068151}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775872068213,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a394a66001B85FkpjKCd5lbi","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a394279001DqSNN8QdTW03I9","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":38395,"input":116,"output":71,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":38208}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775872072868,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a395ca2001L7BAOPNM2nSBFK","messageID":"msg_d7a394a8d0015SGv97bHdl63I8","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872185468,"sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3b12c20010VIUxuEv4Rpx8F","messageID":"msg_d7a394a8d0015SGv97bHdl63I8","sessionID":"ses_285c7aff4ffeNmK0PFKJHA6OXU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ce7cbf41890c4a8aba541318e30c785f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nEnhance the `MetadataService` and related data models to support improved metadata validation, persistence, manipulation, and management capabilities for the AgentCube CLI. This includes enhanced field validation, schema versioning, metadata templates, history tracking, and security scanning.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Enhanced metadata validation\n\n### Requirement: Comprehensive field validation beyond type checking\n\nSystem SHALL provide comprehensive validation for metadata fields including format validation, context-aware validation, and security checks.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates agent name follows DNS-1123 subdomain format\n- Validates entrypoint format based on language\n- Validates image URL format for container registries\n- Validates port range with context warnings for privileged ports\n- Provides clear, actionable error messages\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Validate agent name format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `agent_name` containing invalid characters\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_agent_name` is called with `\"My Agent\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message explaining DNS-1123 subdomain format requirements\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Valid agent name format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `agent_name = \"my-agent-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_agent_name` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation without error\n\n#### Scenario 1.3: Validate Python entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n\n#### Scenario 1.4: Invalid Python entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint = \"javac Main.java\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating mismatch between language and entrypoint\n\n#### Scenario 1.5: Validate Java entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"java\"` and `entrypoint = \"java -jar app.jar\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n\n#### Scenario 1.6: Validate image URL format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `image = {\"url\": \"registry.io/namespace/name:tag\"}`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_image_url` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n\n#### Scenario 1.7: Invalid image URL format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `image = {\"url\": \"invalid-url-format\"}`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_image_url` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message explaining expected container image format\n\n#### Scenario 1.8: Validate privileged port\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `port = 80`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_port_context` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation AND log warning about privileged port requiring special permissions\n\n#### Scenario 1.9: Invalid port range\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with `port = 70000`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_port_context` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be in range 1-65535\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: Metadata migration and versioning\n\n### Requirement: Schema versioning with automatic migration support\n\nSystem SHALL support metadata schema versioning and automatic migration from previous versions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Detects and reads schema version from metadata files\n- Applies automatic migrations for older schema versions\n- Preserves all valid fields during migration\n- Updates schema version after successful migration\n- Rejects metadata with unsupported future schema versions\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: Detect current schema version\n- **GIVEN** an existing `agent_metadata.yaml` with `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read the `schema_version` field and use it to determine migration needs\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Default schema version for legacy files\n- **GIVEN** an existing `agent_metadata.yaml` without `schema_version` field\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL default to version `\"0.0.0\"` (legacy) and apply migrations\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Migrate from legacy format\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version < \"1.0.0\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Apply automatic migrations to convert to current schema\n  - Preserve all valid fields\n  - Map deprecated field names to new ones\n  - Save the migrated metadata with updated `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"`\n\n#### Scenario 2.4: Migrate specific deprecated field\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"0.5.0\"` containing deprecated field `agent_id_old`\n- **WHEN** migration runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Copy value from `agent_id_old` to `agent_id`\n  - Remove `agent_id_old` from migrated metadata\n  - Log the migration action\n\n#### Scenario 2.5: Reject unsupported future schema version\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"2.0.0\"` (newer than supported)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SchemaVersionError` indicating CLI needs to be upgraded\n\n#### Scenario 2.6: No migration for current schema\n- **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"` (current version)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata without applying migrations\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: Metadata merge and override\n\n### Requirement: Robust merge capabilities for combining metadata sources\n\nSystem SHALL provide merge capabilities for combining base metadata from files with CLI option overrides.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Merges CLI options into existing metadata\n- Preserves fields not specified in CLI options\n- Validates merged result\n- Tracks which fields were overridden for logging\n- Handles conflicts appropriately\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: Merge with CLI overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata with `agent_name = \"old-name\"` and CLI option `--agent-name new-name`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Apply CLI override: `agent_name = \"new-name\"`\n  - Preserve other fields not in CLI options\n  - Track that `agent_name` was overridden\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Merge with multiple overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options for multiple fields\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called with `agent_name`, `port`, and `language` overrides\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Apply all CLI overrides\n  - Preserve all other fields\n  - Track all overridden fields\n\n#### Scenario 3.3: Merge with validation failure\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options that conflict (e.g., language mismatch)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Attempt to merge the metadata\n  - Validate the merged result\n  - Raise `ValidationError` if merged metadata is invalid\n\n#### Scenario 3.4: Merge with partial overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata with all fields populated\n- **WHEN** CLI provides only `--port 8080`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Update only the `port` field\n  - Leave all other fields unchanged\n\n#### Scenario 3.5: Merge with new fields\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options for fields not in metadata\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Add the new fields from CLI options\n  - Preserve existing fields\n  - Validate the complete merged result\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: Metadata templates and presets\n\n### Requirement: Template system for common agent patterns\n\nSystem SHALL support metadata templates for common agent patterns and configurations.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Loads built-in templates for common patterns\n- Supports user-defined custom templates\n- Validates template completeness\n- Applies template defaults to new metadata\n- Allows customization after template application\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Load built-in Python template\n- **GIVEN** template name `\"python-fastapi\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load the template from built-in template directory\n  - Return `AgentMetadata` with FastAPI-specific defaults:\n    - `language = \"python\"`\n    - `port = 8000`\n    - `entrypoint = \"uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port {port}\"`\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: Load built-in Java template\n- **GIVEN** template name `\"java-spring\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load the template from built-in template directory\n  - Return `AgentMetadata` with Spring Boot defaults:\n    - `language = \"java\"`\n    - `port = 8080`\n    - `entrypoint = \"java -jar app.jar\"`\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: Load user-defined template\n- **GIVEN** a user template file at `~/.agentcube/templates/my-custom-agent.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called with `\"my-custom-agent\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Search user template directory first\n  - Load the template from user directory\n  - Return `AgentMetadata` with user-defined defaults\n\n#### Scenario 4.4: Template not found\n- **GIVEN** template name `\"nonexistent-template\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TemplateNotFoundError` with helpful message\n\n#### Scenario 4.5: Validate template completeness\n- **GIVEN** a user-defined template file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_template` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Verify template contains all required fields\n  - Warn about optional fields that should be provided by user\n  - Return validation result\n\n#### Scenario 4.6: Apply template to workspace\n- **GIVEN** a workspace without metadata\n- **WHEN** user runs `pack --template python-fastapi`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load the template\n  - Save it as initial metadata\n  - Allow user to customize fields via CLI options\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Metadata validation for deployment\n\n### Requirement: Pre-deployment validation based on provider\n\nSystem SHALL validate metadata requirements specific to the deployment provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates AgentCube provider requirements\n- Validates Kubernetes provider requirements\n- Raises appropriate errors for missing required fields\n- Provides clear error messages with field names\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 5.1: Validate for AgentCube deployment\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify:\n  - `router_url` is present and valid URL\n  - `workload_manager_url` is present and valid URL\n  - `readiness_probe_path` is set\n  - `readiness_probe_port` is set\n\n#### Scenario 5.2: AgentCube deployment missing router_url\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and no `router_url`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DeploymentValidationError` indicating `router_url` is required\n\n#### Scenario 5.3: Validate for Kubernetes deployment\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL verify:\n  - `image.url` is present and valid\n  - `image.tag` is present\n  - `port` is set and valid\n  - `namespace` is set if provided\n\n#### Scenario 5.4: Kubernetes deployment missing image URL\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"k8s\"` and no `image.url`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DeploymentValidationError` indicating image URL is required\n\n#### Scenario 5.5: Validate with all required fields present\n- **GIVEN** metadata with all required fields for the provider\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation without error\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: Metadata serialization and deserialization\n\n### Requirement: Enhanced YAML serialization with comments and environment expansion\n\nSystem SHALL support multiple serialization formats with consistent behavior and helpful output.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Serializes to YAML with helpful comments\n- Excludes None values from output\n- Preserves field order\n- Supports environment variable expansion during deserialization\n- Provides consistent behavior across load/save operations\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 6.1: Serialize to YAML with comments\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Write YAML with helpful comments for each field\n  - Exclude fields with `None` values\n  - Preserve field order from model definition\n\n#### Scenario 6.2: Deserialize with environment variable expansion\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL}\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called with `REGISTRY_URL=\"my-registry.io\"` in environment\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Expand `${REGISTRY_URL}` to `\"my-registry.io\"`\n  - Return metadata with `registry_url = \"my-registry.io\"`\n\n#### Scenario 6.3: Missing required environment variable\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL}\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called without `REGISTRY_URL` in environment\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating required environment variable is not set\n\n#### Scenario 6.4: Default value for missing environment variable\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL:-default-registry.io}\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called without `REGISTRY_URL` in environment\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the default value `\"default-registry.io\"`\n\n#### Scenario 6.5: Preserve field order during save\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object with fields in specific order\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write fields in the same order as in the model definition\n\n#### Scenario 6.6: Exclude None values from output\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object with some optional fields set to `None`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT write fields with `None` values to the YAML file\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Metadata history and rollback\n\n### Requirement: Track metadata changes and support rollback\n\nSystem SHALL track metadata changes over time and support rollback to previous versions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Creates backup of previous metadata before save\n- Stores backups with timestamps\n- Limits backup count to configurable maximum\n- Supports rollback to specific backup version\n- Lists available backup versions\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 7.1: Track metadata changes on save\n- **GIVEN** a workspace with existing metadata\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create a backup of the previous metadata file\n  - Store backup in `.agentcube/metadata_history/` directory\n  - Use filename with timestamp: `agent_metadata_20250411_120000.yaml`\n  - Save new metadata as `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario 7.2: Rollback to previous version\n- **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.rollback_metadata` is called with version `\"20250411_120000\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Restore the specified backup to main metadata file\n  - Create a backup of current metadata before rolling back\n  - Update metadata with appropriate timestamp\n\n#### Scenario 7.3: List metadata history\n- **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.list_metadata_history` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return:\n  - List of available backups with timestamps\n  - Indication of which backup is currently active\n\n#### Scenario 7.4: Limit backup count\n- **GIVEN** metadata history with 15 backups and default limit of 10\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create new backup\n  - Remove oldest backup to maintain limit of 10\n\n#### Scenario 7.5: Configurable backup limit\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `AGENTCUBE_METADATA_HISTORY_LIMIT=5`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL maintain maximum 5 backups\n\n#### Scenario 7.6: No history directory on first save\n- **GIVEN** a workspace without `.agentcube/metadata_history/` directory\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create the directory structure\n  - Save metadata without backup (no previous version exists)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: Metadata validation for security\n\n### Requirement: Security best practices validation\n\nSystem SHALL validate metadata for security best practices and detect potential credential exposure.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Scans for potential credentials in metadata fields\n- Warns about storing credentials in plaintext\n- Validates registry credential configuration\n- Recommends environment variables for sensitive data\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 8.1: Detect API key pattern\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with field containing text matching API key pattern\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Detect potential API key\n  - Return list of fields containing potential credentials\n  - Log warning about credential exposure\n\n#### Scenario 8.2: Detect password pattern\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object with field containing `\"password\": \"secret123\"`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL detect the password pattern and return warning\n\n#### Scenario 8.3: No credentials detected\n- **GIVEN** a metadata object without sensitive patterns\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty list (no credentials found)\n\n#### Scenario 8.4: Validate registry credentials\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `registry_url` requiring authentication\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_registry_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Check if `registry_username` and `registry_password` are present\n  - Warn about storing credentials in plaintext\n  - Recommend using environment variables\n\n#### Scenario 8.5: Registry credentials missing when required\n- **GIVEN** metadata with `registry_url` pointing to private registry\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_registry_credentials` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating credentials are required\n\n#### Scenario 8.6: Recommend environment variables\n- **GIVEN** metadata with plaintext credentials\n- **WHEN** security scan detects credentials\n- **THEN** the system SHALL recommend:\n  - Using environment variables instead\n  - Example: `${REGISTRY_USERNAME}` instead of plaintext value\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Changes\n\n### `AgentMetadata` enhancements\n\nAdd new fields to `AgentMetadata`:\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `schema_version` | `str` | `\"1.0.0\"` | Metadata schema version for migration support |\n| `template_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Name of template used to create this metadata |\n| `metadata_created_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp when metadata was first created |\n| `metadata_updated_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp of last metadata update |\n| `deployment_history` | `Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]]` | `None` | Track deployment attempts and results |\n\nAdd new validators:\n- `validate_agent_name_format` - DNS-1123 subdomain format validation\n- `validate_entrypoint_command` - Language-specific command validation\n- `validate_registry_url` - Container registry URL format validation\n- `validate_schema_version` - Schema version compatibility check\n\n### `MetadataService` new methods\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    # Validation methods\n    def validate_agent_name(self, agent_name: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_entrypoint(self, entrypoint: str, language: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_image_url(self, image_url: str) -> None: ...\n    def validate_port_context(self, port: int) -> None: ...\n\n    # Schema versioning methods\n    def get_schema_version(self, workspace_path: Path) -> str: ...\n    def migrate_metadata(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, from_version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n\n    # Merge methods\n    def merge_metadata(self, base: AgentMetadata, overrides: MetadataOptions) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n\n    # Template methods\n    def load_template(self, template_name: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def validate_template(self, template_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def list_templates(self) -> List[str]: ...\n\n    # Deployment validation methods\n    def validate_for_deployment(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, provider: str) -> None: ...\n\n    # Serialization methods\n    def expand_env_vars(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n\n    # History methods\n    def backup_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Path: ...\n    def rollback_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def list_metadata_history(self, workspace_path: Path) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n    def cleanup_old_backups(self, workspace_path: Path, max_backups: int) -> None: ...\n\n    # Security methods\n    def scan_for_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> List[str]: ...\n    def validate_registry_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### New exception classes\n\n```python\nclass MetadataValidationError(ValidationError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata validation fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass SchemaVersionError(ValueError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata schema version is incompatible\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DeploymentValidationError(MetadataValidationError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when metadata is invalid for deployment\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass TemplateNotFoundError(FileNotFoundError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a requested template is not found\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Template directory structure\n\n```\n~/.agentcube/templates/\n├── python-fastapi.yaml\n├── python-flask.yaml\n├── java-spring.yaml\n├── java-quarkus.yaml\n└── custom/\n    └── (user-defined templates)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.1: Test validation methods\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for validation methods\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Valid and invalid agent name formats\n  - Valid and invalid entrypoint formats for each language\n  - Valid and invalid image URL formats\n  - Port range validation with privileged port warnings\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.2: Test schema migration\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for schema migration\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Migration from legacy to current schema\n  - Migration between multiple schema versions\n  - Field mapping during migration\n  - Schema version rejection for future versions\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.3: Test metadata merge\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for metadata merge\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Simple field override\n  - Multiple field overrides\n  - Merge with validation failure\n  - Partial overrides\n  - New field addition\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.4: Test template loading\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for template loading\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Loading built-in templates\n  - Loading user-defined templates\n  - Template not found error\n  - Template validation\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.5: Test deployment validation\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for deployment validation\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - AgentCube provider validation\n  - Kubernetes provider validation\n  - Missing required fields\n  - Valid configuration\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.6: Test metadata history\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for metadata history\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Backup creation on save\n  - Rollback to specific version\n  - Listing history\n  - Backup count limits\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.7: Test security scanning\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for security scanning\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - API key pattern detection\n  - Password pattern detection\n  - No credentials case\n  - Registry credential validation\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end metadata lifecycle\n- **GIVEN** a new agent workspace\n- **WHEN** user runs:\n  1. `pack --template python-fastapi --agent-name my-agent`\n  2. Modifies metadata file\n  3. Runs `pack --port 9000`\n- **THEN** each operation SHALL:\n  - Use template for initial metadata\n  - Track changes in history\n  - Apply overrides correctly\n  - Validate all changes\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.2: Schema migration on existing workspace\n- **GIVEN** an existing workspace with legacy metadata\n- **WHEN** user runs `pack`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Detect legacy schema\n  - Apply automatic migration\n  - Update schema version\n  - Log migration actions\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Metadata Validation\n\n- [ ] All validation methods accept valid inputs without error\n- [ ] All validation methods reject invalid inputs with clear error messages\n- [ ] Agent name validation enforces DNS-1123 subdomain format\n- [ ] Entrypoint validation is language-specific\n- [ ] Image URL validation enforces container registry format\n- [ ] Port validation includes context warnings for privileged ports\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Schema Versioning\n\n- [ ] Schema version is detected from metadata files\n- [ ] Legacy files default to version \"0.0.0\"\n- [ ] Automatic migration works for at least 2 previous schema versions\n- [ ] Future schema versions are rejected with upgrade message\n- [ ] Migrated metadata has updated schema version\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Metadata Merge\n\n- [ ] CLI options override metadata file values\n- [ ] Fields not in CLI options are preserved\n- [ ] Merged metadata is validated\n- [ ] Override tracking works for logging\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Templates\n\n- [ ] Built-in templates load successfully\n- [ ] User-defined templates load from correct location\n- [ ] Missing templates raise appropriate error\n- [ ] Template validation works correctly\n- [ ] Template application creates valid metadata\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Deployment Validation\n\n- [ ] AgentCube provider validates required fields\n- [ ] Kubernetes provider validates required fields\n- [ ] Missing required fields raise `DeploymentValidationError`\n- [ ] Valid configurations pass validation\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Serialization\n\n- [ ] YAML output includes helpful comments\n- [ ] None values are excluded from output\n- [ ] Field order is preserved\n- [ ] Environment variables are expanded correctly\n- [ ] Missing environment variables raise `ValidationError`\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - History and Rollback\n\n- [ ] Backups are created before each save\n- [ ] Backup filenames include timestamps\n- [ ] Rollback restores specified version\n- [ ] History listing returns all backups\n- [ ] Backup count limits are enforced\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Security\n\n- [ ] Credential scanning detects common patterns\n- [ ] Warnings are logged for detected credentials\n- [ ] Registry credential validation works correctly\n- [ ] Environment variable recommendations are provided\n\n### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Metadata operations complete within 100ms for typical workspaces\n- [ ] Validation error messages are clear and actionable\n- [ ] Migration process is backwards compatible\n- [ ] Template system is extensible for user-defined templates\n- [ ] History management is efficient (max 10 backups by default)\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all new methods with >= 90% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end workflows\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Enhanced with validation, migration, merge, template, history, and security methods\n   - Maintains backwards compatibility with existing methods\n\n2. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Extended with new fields for schema versioning, templates, timestamps, and history\n   - New validators for comprehensive field validation\n\n3. **Template System** (`agentcube/templates/` and `~/.agentcube/templates/`)\n   - Built-in templates for common agent patterns\n   - Support for user-defined custom templates\n\n4. **Metadata History** (`.agentcube/metadata_history/`)\n   - Automatic backup creation\n   - Timestamp-based versioning\n   - Configurable backup limits\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n#### Validation Algorithm\n1. For each field requiring validation:\n   - Apply format-specific validation rules\n   - Check context-specific constraints (e.g., privileged ports)\n   - Raise `ValidationError` with descriptive message on failure\n\n#### Migration Algorithm\n1. Read `schema_version` from metadata\n2. If version < current version:\n   - Apply migration functions in sequence\n   - Map deprecated fields to new ones\n   - Update `schema_version` to current\n3. If version > current version:\n   - Raise `SchemaVersionError`\n\n#### Merge Algorithm\n1. Start with base metadata from file\n2. For each field in CLI options:\n   - Override base value if option is provided\n   - Track which fields were overridden\n3. Validate merged result\n4. Return merged metadata with tracking info\n\n#### Backup Algorithm\n1. Check if existing metadata file exists\n2. If yes:\n   - Generate timestamp for backup filename\n   - Copy existing file to `.agentcube/metadata_history/`\n   - Check backup count and remove oldest if over limit\n3. Save new metadata to main file\n\n#### Security Scan Algorithm\n1. Define credential pattern regexes (API keys, passwords, tokens)\n2. For each string field in metadata:\n   - Check against each pattern\n   - If match found, add field to results\n3. Return list of fields with potential credentials\n4. Log warnings and recommendations\n\n---\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\n### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n\nSystem SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation and serialization\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing and generation\n- `python-dateutil` for timestamp handling\n\n### Requirement: File locations\n\n- MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- AgentMetadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Built-in templates: `agentcube/templates/`\n- User templates: `~/.agentcube/templates/`\n- Metadata history: `.agentcube/metadata_history/`\n- Primary metadata file: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Requirement: Configuration\n\n- Backup count limit: Environment variable `AGENTCUBE_METADATA_HISTORY_LIMIT` (default: 10)\n- Template directories: Built-in + `~/.agentcube/templates/`\n- Current schema version: `\"1.0.0\"`\n\n---\n\n## Related Requirements\n\n- **AR-020:** CLI pack command (uses MetadataService)\n- **AR-021:** CLI build command (uses MetadataService)\n- **AR-022:** CLI publish command (uses MetadataService)\n- **AR-023:** CLI invoke/status commands (uses MetadataService)\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md:** Base design for MetadataService and AgentMetadata\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md:** Base specification for metadata handling","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872185187,"end":1775872185464}}}}
